narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Historical knowledge about the Anglo-Saxon and Viking age and the relationships between Anglo-Saxons and Vikings.
I have learnt greatly about distinguishing historical facts from commercial fiction supposedly based on those facts. Surprisingly, I also feel that my essay writing skills have improved greatly.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: We had some great field trips, especially the one to York which enhanced our learning experience. Reading primary sources like the Anglo-Saxon Chronicle and Beowulf was interesting and helpful. Most of us didn't come into this course with a lot of knowledge about this time period/these people so more lecture/instruction on the subject would have been helpful before diving into our own discussions.

Strengths: Exciting topic, given the hype from the TV series Vikings. The course is very illuminating about the culture and long-lasting effects of the Viking age in England. The course also helps hone critical thinking and strong analysis of primary sources. Weakness: The structure of the course is quite messy.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes but only if the course topic interests them. If not, the motivation to keep working may wane quickly.
